  "prompt": "What's wrong with Quora?",
  "response": "Quora has several commonly cited criticisms:\n\n1. Quality of answers varies widely\n- Many low-quality or opinionated responses\n- Some answers seem unreliable or poorly researched\n\n2. Moderation issues\n- Inconsistent moderation policies\n- Potential for bias in content removal\n- Some users feel unfairly banned or restricted\n\n3. User experience problems\n- Aggressive pop-ups asking users to sign up\n- Intrusive ads\n- Paywalls blocking content\n\n4. Content repetition\n- Similar questions get asked repeatedly\n- Some topics become echo chambers\n\n5. Privacy concerns\n- Requires extensive personal information\n- Algorithms can feel invasive\n\n6. Community dynamics\n- Can have toxic or argumentative interactions\n- Some perceived elitism among top contributors\n\n7. Business model challenges\n- Struggles to monetize effectively\n- Difficulty maintaining high-quality content\n\nThese issues don't mean Quora is entirely bad, but they represent common criticisms from users and observers. Individual experiences can vary significantly.",
